# Accionator Project Overview

## Project Description
Accionator is a Next.js 15 application with a Convex backend focused on financial data analysis and stock/sector tracking. The application uses modern React patterns, TypeScript, and includes features for token usage tracking and historical data analysis.

## Tech Stack
- **Frontend**: Next.js 15 with App Router, React 19, TypeScript
- **Backend**: Convex (real-time database and backend)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS 4.1, Radix UI components
- **Authentication**: Clerk
- **Data Visualization**: Nivo charts
- **State Management**: TanStack React Query
- **Package Manager**: pnpm

## Project Structure

### Root Directory
- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Project dependencies and scripts
- [next.config.ts](mdc:next.config.ts) - Next.js configuration
- [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) - TypeScript configuration
- [eslint.config.mjs](mdc:eslint.config.mjs) - ESLint configuration
- [.prettierrc](mdc:.prettierrc) - Prettier configuration
- [components.json](mdc:components.json) - UI components configuration

### Source Code (`src/`)
- [src/app/](mdc:src/app) - Next.js App Router pages and layouts
- [src/components/](mdc:src/components) - Reusable React components
- @src/components/ui - React component atoms
- [src/lib/](mdc:src/lib) - Utility functions and configurations
- [src/hooks/](mdc:src/hooks) - Custom React hooks
- [src/queries/](mdc:src/queries) - ReactQuery query functions
- [src/mutations/](mdc:src/mutations) - ReactQuery mutation functions
- [src/server/](mdc:src/server) - Server-side utilities

### Backend (`convex/`)
- [convex/schema.ts](mdc:convex/schema.ts) - Database schema definition
- [convex/auth.config.ts](mdc:convex/auth.config.ts) - Authentication configuration
- [convex/queries/](mdc:convex/queries) - Database query functions
- [convex/mutations/](mdc:convex/mutations) - Database mutation functions
- [convex/helpers/](mdc:convex/helpers) - Shared utility functions

## Key Features
- User authentication and authorization
- Token usage tracking and limits
- Stock and sector search tracking
- Historical usage analytics
- Real-time data with Convex
- Financial data visualization with Nivo charts

## Development Commands
- `pnpm dev` - Start development server with Turbopack
- `pnpm build` - Build for production
- `pnpm lint` - Run ESLint
- `pnpm prettier` - Format code with Prettier
- `pnpm check` - Run linting and formatting fixes
